org.opensha2.data

Interface Data3D


  • public interface Data3D
    A wrapper around a 3D table (or volume) of double-valued data that is arranged according to strictly increasing and uniformly spaced double-valued keys. Data tables are almost always used to represent binned data, and so while row and column keys are bin centers, indexing is managed internally using bin edges. This simplifies issues related to rounding/precision errors that occur when indexing according to explicit double values.

    To create a Data3D instance, use a Data3D.Builder.

    Internally, a Data3D is backed by a double[][][] array where 'row' refers to the 1st dimension, 'column' the second dimension, and 'level' the 3rd.

    Note that data tables are not intended for use with very high precision data and keys are currently limited to a precision of 4 decimal places. This may be changed or improved in the future.

    Author:
    Peter Powers
